features.text:
IWAB is a women-led organization with a mission to support, empower and provide a voice to the diverse creatives and artists at the forefront of the NFT movement.  As early adopters of this rapidly evolving ecosystem, IWAB advocates for NFT literacy and engagement with the collaborators, creators, and artists who are laying the foundation for this new movement today.  Although not a new paradigm, digital art has been with us for decades, it is a new and adapted medium that is taking art and collectables from mere interaction to a burgeoning community. Community being an integral part of the movement is a fundamental component of what we think of as culture today.

 

IWAB’s interest lies in the intersection of the traditional art world and the NFT space as this newly adapted digital world continues to unfold. The evolution has granted access to an otherwise impenetrable industry allowing artists to break through and open doors to talented individuals who were struggling to have their voices heard.

 

IWAB is led by Krista Howard, a top 100 art advisor and Daniela Luzi Tudor, a serial entrepreneur and musician; both leaders and innovators in their respective industries.  Philanthropists and supporters of diverse communities are each looking to serve the community in the growing NFT space.
